  "keyFeatures": [
    "Converts AsciiDoc source to HTML 5, DocBook 5, and man page formats",
    "Extensible via a rich extension API (preprocessors, block processors, inline macro processors, etc.)",
    "CLI tool (asciidoctor command) and Ruby API for programmatic use",
    "Built-in syntax highlighting via Rouge, highlight.js, and Pygments",
    "Custom converter support via Tilt-supported templates",
    "Multiple safe modes (unsafe, safe, server, secure) for controlled environments",
    "Runs on CRuby, JRuby, and TruffleRuby; also available as AsciidoctorJ (JVM) and Asciidoctor.js",
    "Default stylesheet with Font Awesome icons and MathJax STEM support"
  ],
